725228f-a.title: Queens: 33rd Street - 20th Road
725228f-a.text:
33rd Street, north from 20th Road toward the East River
waterfront industrial area. The garage (left) is at the S.W.
corner of 20th Avenue. The Dietn coal silo is on a canal at
19th Avenue, and to its right is the Steinway piano factory.
P. L. Sperr  June 3, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS

725094f-c.title: Queens: 20th Road - 33rd Street
725094f-c.text:
20Ch(91d Bowery Baj Road, north side, east of 33rd Street, showing at
the left foreground the home of George Kouwenhoven. At the right
(center of view) is shown the family burial place of the Lawrence and
Leverich families. In the background is the home of Peter Luyster.
The owner of this farm was William Lawrence from 170O-1732. He was
followed by John Leverich in 1732, and William Leverich later, who had
possession until 1754. George Eowenhoven was the owner from 1852-1860.
Francis Durye Kouwenhoven erected (or remodeled f) this house in 1857.
Harry Puschea Williams who married into the Lowenhoven family is the
present owner of the house. This house, seen in a set of four views,
was no llonger standing in May 1929.
May 1923.
Views 1 \& 4.
View 2: 1922.
View 3: March 1923.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725096f-a.title: Queens: 20th Road - 33rd Street
725096f-a.text:
(1)
20th (01d Bowery Bad Road (along front of Geo. Kouwenhoven house seen at
left), between 33rd and 36th Streets. This is a rear view of the Lawrence
family's private cemetery taken from 21st Ave. Eventually it will be
oremoved because it is in the direct line of the extension of 35th Street.
In the background are the Steinway and Sons piano and foundry factories.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

725101f-b.title: Queens: 20th Road - 33rd Street
725101f-b.text:
20th Road,(91d Bowery Road,) west of 36th Street to 33rd Street,
showing at the right the Geo. Eouwenhoven farmhouse, demolished in
May 1929. At the left is the entrance to the Lawrence family cemetery.
This is a set of three views.
May 1925.
View 2: March 1923.
View 3: May 1923.
